definition.value: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoyl and hexadecanoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoyl and linoleoyl  respectively.
An insecticide alkaloid isolated from South American plant Ryania speciosa.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl and (11Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.
A 17beta-hydroxy steroid that is 17beta-estradiol in which the hydrogen at position 2 has been replaced by a hydroxy group and the phenolic hydrogen at position 3 has bee replaced by a methyl group.
A glutathione conjugate in which the thiol hydrogen of glutathione has been replaced by a 2,4-dinitrophenyl group.
A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by methyl and methylsulfanyl groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively. It is a metabolite found in coffee and human urine.
